article.headline: Tennessee St. 59, Morehead St. 53
article.story: NASHVILLE, Tenn. (AP) -- Bruce Price scored 11 points and was the only Tennessee State player in double figures in a 59-53 win Thursday over Morehead. Nine players scored for the Tigers (5-7, 2-1 Ohio Valley Conference), who led most of the way. Morehead (4-8, 2-3 OVC) got to within 3 points in the second half after trailing 28-18 at halftime. Morehead, which shot just 36 percent for the game, was led by Jamyron Steward with 15 points and Maze Stallworth with 12. The Tigers shot 52.4 percent including 6-of-10 3-pointers. Morehead hit just 5-of-18 3-pointers.
